# Security Patterns

## Authentication
- Use MSS (medinovai-security-service) via SecurityClient SDK
- NEVER implement local auth/login
- JWT validation on ALL protected routes
- CORS: specific origins only, NEVER wildcard `*`

## Authorization
- Dynamic authorization via SpiceDB (ReBAC)
- NEVER hardcode roles or permissions
- Check permissions at API boundary, not in business logic

## PHI/PII Protection
- Encrypt PHI at rest (encryption-vault) and in transit (TLS 1.3)
- Log PHI access as audit events
- Validate user has permission before ANY PHI access
- NEVER log raw PHI values — use IDs only
- Consent check before data use

## Secrets
- All secrets via secrets-manager-bridge
- NEVER in .env files, config, or code
- NEVER commit secrets to git
